{
  "texts": [
    "For this goal, the unclear relation between prediction and explanation is particularly problematic, therefore properties such as illustrative elements may be less desired.",
    "selectivity and subjectivity can also be limiting factors, albeit inevitable in many situations.",
    "Even incomplete and subjective explanations can however be useful if the developer observes a consistency in the explanations including or lacking the desired reasoning process.",
    "Explaining wrong labels may be a useful feature, too, as it can display the falla-cies of the model.",
    "As a result, the developer may make targeted modifications to the training data, such as mitigating unwanted statistical cues."
  ]
}